SIMPLE: sportful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sportful
<hw>Sport"ful</hw> <pr>(-f⟦usdot⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Full of sport; merry; frolicsome; full of jesting; indulging in
mirth or play; playful; wanton; <as>as, a <ex>sportful</ex>
companion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Down he alights among the <qex>sportful</qex> herd.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Done in jest, or for mere play; sportive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They are no <qex>sportful</qex> productions of the soil.</q>
<rj><qau>Bentley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sport"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sport"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sporting</ent>⟦br⟧
